    "title": "chevron-right",
    "text": "PORTLAND (WGME) -- Authorities say they seized a significant amount of drugs and arrested a Maine man for trafficking fentanyl and cocaine in Portland. For the past three months, the MDEA says agents and Portland police officers have been investigating 27-year-old Charles Aboda of Portland for drug trafficking in the city. The MDEA say Aboda was selling large quantities of drugs as well as making street level sales to local drug users. During the investigation, the MDEA says undercover agents bought drugs from Aboda. Agents arrested Aboda on Tuesday and charged him with unlawful aggravated trafficking in schedule drugs (fentanyl) and unlawful trafficking in schedule drugs (cocaine). At the time of his arrest, the MDEA says agents seized approximately 3 ounces of fentanyl and cocaine as well as $1,000 in suspected drug proceeds. The MDEA says agents also searched a home in the West End area of Portland in connection with the drug trafficking investigation and found approximately 2 ounces of fentanyl, cocaine, crack cocaine, and methamphetamine as well as a loaded handgun and approximately $10,000 in suspected drug proceeds. Aboda was taken to the Cumberland County Jail. His bail has been set at $15,000 cash.",
